Why “flank” is the right metaphor

Head-on defenses look at whether the object is valid.

Flanking defenses look at:
	•	what changed right before validity
	•	what adjacent conditions made the transition possible
	•	whether the surrounding pattern matches the expected field

So Gatejackal does not ask only:

“Is this valid?”

It asks:

“Is this valid in the way it became valid?”

That is the ambush point.

