OrbitOS mapping

In OrbitOS terms, Gatejackal sits at a state vector hinge and watches for unauthorized force injection.

A transition becomes:

S(t) --operator/context--> S(t+1)

Gatejackal computes:
	•	expected operator
	•	expected delta
	•	expected conservation rules

If the observed delta is too large, too clean, mistimed, or grants disproportionate leverage, it flags it as likely off-manifold.

That is the NL ambush in dynamical language:
catch the state jump that does not fit the field.

